commit f768cc51f7843584e0b8569a5b0cea997d51ef6e
Author: Mathias Fussenegger <f.mathias@zignar.net>
Date:   Tue Jan 9 17:01:56 2024 +0100

    Fix type signature of unnest with single argument
    
    In
    
        SELECT x FROM unnest([[1, 2,], [3]]) as t (x)
    
    `x` got typed as `int[]`, not accounting for the unnest behavior of the
    function. This led to `ClassCastException` errors.
    
    Two or more arguments worked because we had a dedicated signature.
    
    Fixes https://github.com/crate/crate/issues/15306
    
    (cherry picked from commit 28f8a4b4765ab933f6f4efebaf5bbadb61ff7b9b)

